Read in data

First we read in the performance results

results=dir(resfol,pattern="eval")
allres=NULL
for(thisres in results){
  test=scan(paste0(resfol,thisres),what="char")
  if(length(test)>0){
    read.table(paste0(resfol,thisres))->x
    clean_name=gsub("-tags.*","",thisres)
    unit=gsub(".*txt_","",thisres)
    unit=gsub("\\..*","",unit)
    algo=gsub(".eval.*","",thisres)
    algo=gsub(paste0(".*",unit,"."),"",algo)
    allres=rbind(allres,cbind(t(as.numeric(as.character(x[,-1]))),thisres,clean_name,algo,unit))
  }
}
colnames(allres)[1:dim(x)[1]]<-c(as.character(x[,1]))
write.table(allres,"derived/results.txt",quote=F,sep="\t")

Next we read the corpus characteristics descriptions and combine them with the above.

read.table("derived/results.txt",header=T)->allres

library(jsonlite)
statsres=dir(resfol,pattern="stats")
allstats=NULL
for(thisstat in statsres){
  fromJSON(paste0(resfol,thisstat), flatten=TRUE)->x
  clean_name=gsub("-tags.*","",thisstat)
  nphone_tokens=x$phones$tokens
  nphone_types=x$phones$types
  nsyllable_tokens=x$syllables$tokens
  nsyllable_types=x$syllables$types
  nwords_tokens=x$words$tokens
  nwords_types=x$words$types
  nword_hapax=x$words$hapaxes
  mattr=x$corpus$mattr
  entropy=x$corpus$entropy
  nutts_single_word=x$corpus$nutts_single_word
  nutts=x$corpus$nutts
  allstats=rbind(allstats,cbind(clean_name,nphone_tokens,nphone_types,
                                        nsyllable_tokens,nsyllable_types,
                                nwords_tokens,nwords_types,
                                nword_hapax,mattr,
                                entropy,
                                nutts_single_word,nutts))
}

write.table(allstats,"derived/stats.txt",quote=F,sep="\t")
read.table("derived/stats.txt",header=T)->allstats #this inelegant write-out-read-in so that all cols are numeric
#calculate some proportions to capture tendency to have single-word utterances and to have words that are not repeated controlling to a certain extent for corpus size
allstats$prop_swu=allstats$nutts_single_word/allstats$nutts
allstats$prop_hap=allstats$nword_hapax/allstats$nwords_types
allstats$avg_ph_w=allstats$nphone_tokens/allstats$nwords_tokens
allstats$avg_syl_w=allstats$nsyllable_tokens/allstats$nwords_tokens
allstats$avg_w_utt=allstats$nwords_tokens/allstats$nutts
write.table(allstats,"derived/stats.txt",quote=F,sep="\t")


merge(allres,allstats,by="clean_name")->allres_stat
write.table(allres_stat,"derived/all.txt",quote=F,sep="\t")

Notice we explain a whopping >90% of the variance with just these two variables and their interaction. The stats simply confirm what is visually obvious below. In the following graph, we show the effects of unit and algorithm.

In short, we observe clear effects of basic unit (+ for syllables, circles for phones) and algorithm, and an important interaction between the two.

To be able to focus on other predictors, in some of the following analyses, we’ll use the residuals from above.

res$res_ua<-residuals(minfit)

Corpus size effects

Corpus size can be measured in number of phones, words, utterances. To decide which of the three we’ll use in further analyses, we inspect the proportion of variance explained by each.

for(thispred in c("nphone_tokens","nsyllable_tokens","nwords_tokens","nutts")){
  myfit=lm(res$token_fscore~res$algo*res$unit*res[,thispred] + (1/res$clean_name))
  print(thispred)
  print(summary(myfit)$adj.r.squared)
}

Further exploration of the role of corpus length

library(jsonlite)
for(thisfol in dir(resfol_conc)){
  # dir(resfol_conc)[3]->thisfol
  thispath=paste0(resfol_conc,"/",thisfol,"/")
  leval=dir(path=thispath,pattern="eval")
  allres=NULL
  for(thisres in leval){
   # leval[1]->thisres
   test=scan(paste0(thispath,thisres),what="char")
    if(length(test)>0){
      read.table(paste0(thispath,thisres))->x
      x[,"V2"]<-as.numeric(as.character(x[,"V2"]))
      clean_name=gsub("_.*","",thisres)
      unit=gsub(".*phone.*","phone",gsub(".*syllable.*","syllable",thisres))
      algo=gsub("^[0-9]*_","",thisres) 
      algo=gsub("dibsb","dibs_b",gsub("_","",gsub(fixed=T,".","",gsub(unit,"",gsub(".txt","",gsub(".eval","",algo))))))
      allres=rbind(allres,cbind(t(x[,-1]),thisfol,thisres,clean_name,algo,unit))
    }
  }
  colnames(allres)[1:dim(x)[1]]<-c(as.character(x[,1]))
  write.table(allres,paste0("derived/length_results_",thisfol,".txt"),quote=F,sep="\t")
  
  
  statsres=dir(path=thispath,pattern="stats")
  allstats=NULL
  for(thisstat in statsres){
    fromJSON(paste0(thispath,thisstat), flatten=TRUE)->x
    clean_name=gsub("_.*","",thisstat)
    nphone_tokens=x$phones$tokens
    nphone_types=x$phones$types
    nsyllable_tokens=x$syllables$tokens
    nsyllable_types=x$syllables$types
    nwords_tokens=x$words$tokens
    nwords_types=x$words$types
    
  #!! this is a patch, fix for the replication
    nword_hapax=x$corpus$nword_hapax
    if(is.null(nword_hapax))  nword_hapax=x$words$hapaxes
    mattr=x$corpus$mattr
    entropy=x$corpus$entropy
    nutts_single_word=x$corpus$nutts_single_word
    nutts=x$corpus$nutts
    allstats=rbind(allstats,cbind(clean_name,nphone_tokens,nphone_types,
                                  nsyllable_tokens,nsyllable_types,
                                  nwords_tokens,nwords_types,
                                  nword_hapax,mattr,
                                  entropy,
                                  nutts_single_word,nutts))
  }
  
  write.table(allstats,paste0("derived/length_stats_",thisfol,".txt"),quote=F,sep="\t")
  read.table(paste0("derived/length_stats_",thisfol,".txt"),header=T)->allstats #this inelegant write-out-read-in so that all cols are numeric
  #calculate some proportions to capture tendency to have single-word utterances and to have words that are not repeated controlling to a certain extent for corpus size
  allstats$prop_swu=allstats$nutts_single_word/allstats$nutts
  allstats$prop_hap=allstats$nword_hapax/allstats$nwords_types
  allstats$avg_ph_w=allstats$nphone_tokens/allstats$nwords_tokens
  allstats$avg_syl_w=allstats$nsyllable_tokens/allstats$nwords_tokens
  allstats$avg_w_utt=allstats$nwords_tokens/allstats$nutts
  write.table(allstats,paste0("derived/length_stats_",thisfol,".txt"),quote=F,sep="\t")
  
  merge(allres,allstats,by="clean_name")->allres_stat
  write.table(allres_stat,paste0("derived/length_all_",thisfol,".txt"),quote=F,sep="\t")
}
